                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17881438" author="chia7712" created="Fri, 13 Sep 2024 01:07:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-17077&quot; title=&quot;the node.id is inconsistent to broker.id when &amp;quot;broker.id.generation.enable=true&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-17077&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-17077&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;? I had saw the incorrect node.id in migration before, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-17077&quot; title=&quot;the node.id is inconsistent to broker.id when &amp;quot;broker.id.generation.enable=true&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-17077&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-17077&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was filed to fix that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17881620" author="cmccabe" created="Fri, 13 Sep 2024 16:38:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue is that the situation described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-17077&quot; title=&quot;the node.id is inconsistent to broker.id when &amp;quot;broker.id.generation.enable=true&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-17077&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-17077&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; should not happen in the first place &amp;#8211; id generation should be disabled before we do migration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17881973" author="scholzj" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2024 08:53:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cmccabe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cmccabe&quot;&gt;cmccabe&lt;/a&gt; The name of the issue seems a bit misleading. The commit I found seems to check that the broker ID generation is not used (i.e. the broker ID is not set to -1). But the name of the issue here seems to suggests that &lt;tt&gt;broker.id.generation.enable&lt;/tt&gt; needs to be disabled. Would it make sense to update the issue name to make it less confusing (especially if it for example gets into the release notes)?&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17881987" author="chia7712" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2024 10:04:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=scholzj&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;scholzj&quot;&gt;scholzj&lt;/a&gt; yes, the message is a bit unmatched. Do you want to submit a patch to revise them?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17882035" author="scholzj" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2024 13:23:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=chia7712&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;chia7712&quot;&gt;chia7712&lt;/a&gt; I was mainly concerned by the Jira name as I guess that goes to the release notes. But you are right, the error message might be a bit confusing as well. I can open a PR for it. How does it work for the 3.9 release? Do I open it directly against the 3.9 branch? Or do I open it against trunk and it will be later cherry-picked?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17882092" author="chia7712" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2024 14:59:18 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;Or do I open it against trunk and it will be later cherry-picked?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this one &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17882104" author="scholzj" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2024 15:44:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=chia7712&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;chia7712&quot;&gt;chia7712&lt;/a&gt; Ok, I opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/17210&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/17210&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
